a3ComQosGenClassTable.name: a3ComQosGenClassTable
a3ComQosGenClassTable.description: This table lists all QoS classes (Flow and Non-Flow) configured in the system.

a3ComQosGenClassEntry.name: a3ComQosGenClassEntry
a3ComQosGenClassEntry.description: An entry describing a single class entity.

a3ComQosGenClassIndex.name: a3ComQosGenClassIndex
a3ComQosGenClassIndex.description: A unique value for each entry.

a3ComQosGenClassName.name: a3ComQosGenClassName
a3ComQosGenClassName.description: A textual name for the class.

a3ComQosGenClassControlId.name: a3ComQosGenClassControlId
a3ComQosGenClassControlId.description: The control entry that this class is associated with. Note that the user must have created the control (via the a3ComQosCtrlTable) before making the association via this object. A value of zero indicates no control is attached.

a3ComQosFlowClassTable.name: a3ComQosFlowClassTable
a3ComQosFlowClassTable.description: This table lists the Flow classes defined in the system. A Flow class applies only to IP unicast and multicast packets. A Flow class is defined in terms of the IP packet header: IP protocol type, IP source and destination addresses, TCP/UDP source and destination ports. Note that a filter entry can only be modified if there is no control attached to it. Otherwise, the entry has to be deleted and recreated.

a3ComQosFlowClassEntry.name: a3ComQosFlowClassEntry
a3ComQosFlowClassEntry.description: An entry describing a single flow class entity.

a3ComQosFlowClassIndex.name: a3ComQosFlowClassIndex
a3ComQosFlowClassIndex.description: A unique value for each entry. Flow classses use id values between 1-399.

a3ComQosFlowClassFilterIndex.name: a3ComQosFlowClassFilterIndex
a3ComQosFlowClassFilterIndex.description: The unique filter index associated with this class. Note that the maximum limit of 100 filters is the aggregate of all the filters defined in the system, not just the number of filters defined for this classifier.

a3ComQosFlowClassCastType.name: a3ComQosFlowClassCastType
a3ComQosFlowClassCastType.description: The network layer cast type for this class.

a3ComQosFlowClassIpProtoType.name: a3ComQosFlowClassIpProtoType
a3ComQosFlowClassIpProtoType.description: The IP protocol type for this class.

a3ComQosFlowClassSrcAddr.name: a3ComQosFlowClassSrcAddr
a3ComQosFlowClassSrcAddr.description: The source IP address for this class.

a3ComQosFlowClassSrcSubnetMask.name: a3ComQosFlowClassSrcSubnetMask
a3ComQosFlowClassSrcSubnetMask.description: The source subnet mask for this class.

a3ComQosFlowClassDestAddr.name: a3ComQosFlowClassDestAddr
a3ComQosFlowClassDestAddr.description: The destination IP address for this class.

a3ComQosFlowClassDestSubnetMask.name: a3ComQosFlowClassDestSubnetMask
a3ComQosFlowClassDestSubnetMask.description: The destination subnet mask for this class.

a3ComQosFlowClassPortStart.name: a3ComQosFlowClassPortStart
a3ComQosFlowClassPortStart.description: The starting range of ports associated with this class.

a3ComQosFlowClassPortEnd.name: a3ComQosFlowClassPortEnd
a3ComQosFlowClassPortEnd.description: The finishing range of ports associated with this class.

a3ComQosFlowClassRowStatus.name: a3ComQosFlowClassRowStatus
a3ComQosFlowClassRowStatus.description: The status column for this entry. This object can be set to: createAndGo(4) destroy(6) The following value may be read: active(1) Setting this object to createAndGo(4) creates a row in in this table. The agent will allocate the next sequential filter index value for the newly created entry. Setting this object to destroy(6) will remove this entry. Note that only the entry with the highest a3ComQosFlowClassFilterIndex value can be deleted. Also, an entry can only be deleted if there is no control attached to it.

a3ComQosNonFlowClassTable.name: a3ComQosNonFlowClassTable
a3ComQosNonFlowClassTable.description: This table lists the Non-Flow classes defined in the system. A Non-Flow class defines a packet in terms of its data link level protocol: IEEE 802.1p tag value, cast type (broadcast, multicast, and unicast). Packets which match a Non-Flow class receive a service level specific to that class.

a3ComQosNonFlowClassEntry.name: a3ComQosNonFlowClassEntry
a3ComQosNonFlowClassEntry.description: An entry describing a single non-flow class entity.

a3ComQosNonFlowClassIndex.name: a3ComQosNonFlowClassIndex
a3ComQosNonFlowClassIndex.description: A unique value for each entry. Non-flow classs use class ids values between 400-499.

a3ComQosNonFlowClassCastType.name: a3ComQosNonFlowClassCastType
a3ComQosNonFlowClassCastType.description: A bit mask of 'cast' types associated with this class. Each cast is represented by a single bit. If that bit is set then the corresponding cast is selected by this class. The following bits are currently defined: Unicast 0x01 Multicast 0x02 Broadcast 0x04

a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtos.name: a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtos
a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtos.description: A bit mask of network protocols associated with this class. Each protocol is represented by a single bit. If that bit is set then the corresponding protocol is a member of this class. Only one protocol can be assigned to any given classifier. This object CAN ONLY BE SET if a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtoDesciptor is set to name(1) for the associated class. Custom (0x10) will be returned if a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtoDesciptor is not set to name(1). However this object CANNOT be set to Custom. The following bits are currently defined: Any 0x00 IP 0x01 IPX 0x02 TCP 0x04 Appletalk 0x08 Custom 0x10

a3ComQosNonFlowClass8021pTags.name: a3ComQosNonFlowClass8021pTags
a3ComQosNonFlowClass8021pTags.description: A bit mask of the 802.1p tags associated with this class. Each tag is represented by a single bit. If that bit is set then the corresponding tag is selected by this class. The following bits are currently defined: 8021pTag-0 0x01 8021pTag-1 0x02 8021pTag-2 0x04 8021pTag-3 0x08 8021pTag-4 0x10 8021pTag-5 0x20 8021pTag-6 0x40 8021pTag-7 0x80

a3ComQosNonFlowClassRowStatus.name: a3ComQosNonFlowClassRowStatus
a3ComQosNonFlowClassRowStatus.description: The status column for this entry. This object can be set to: createAndGo(4) destroy(6) The following value may be read: active(1) Setting this object to createAndGo(4) creates a row in in this table. Setting this object to destroy(6) will remove this entry. Note that an entry can only be deleted if there is no control attached to it.

a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtoDescriptor.name: a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtoDescriptor
a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtoDescriptor.description: This object determines whether a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtos or a3ComQosNonFlowClassCustomProto is used to define the protocol for a classifier. If set to name(1), the pre-defined types Any, IP, IPX, TCP, AppleTalk from a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtos will be used. If set to ethertype(2) or dsap-ssap(3) then the a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtos will be custom and the value used will be determined by a3ComQosNonFlowClassCustomProto.

a3ComQosNonFlowClassCustomProto.name: a3ComQosNonFlowClassCustomProto
a3ComQosNonFlowClassCustomProto.description: This object determines a 2-byte hex value for the Ethertype or DSAP/SSAP that will be used in conjunction with a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtoDescriptor. If a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtoDescriptor is set to name(1) then this object is not used and it CANNOT be set. If a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtoDescriptor is set to ethertype(2) then the value will be used as an ethertype mask. If a3ComQosNonFlowClassProtoDescriptor is set to dsap-ssap(3) then the most significant byte will be used for the DSAP value and the least significant will be used for the SSAP value. -- Example 1: a3ComQosNonFlowClassProto is set to ethertype (2) a3ComQosNonFlowClassCustomTypeMask is set to 0x1234 The value 0x1234 will be used in the ethertype field. -- Example 2: a3ComQosNonFlowClassCustomType is set to dsap-ssap (2) a3ComQosNonFlowClassCustomTypeMask is set to 0x1234 The value 0x12 would be used for the DSAP value. The value 0x34 would be used for the SSAP value.

a3ComQosCtrlTable.name: a3ComQosCtrlTable
a3ComQosCtrlTable.description: A list of controls defined on a given system.

a3ComQosCtrlEntry.name: a3ComQosCtrlEntry
a3ComQosCtrlEntry.description: An entry describing a single QoS control.

a3ComQosCtrlIndex.name: a3ComQosCtrlIndex
a3ComQosCtrlIndex.description: A unique value for this entry.

a3ComQosCtrlName.name: a3ComQosCtrlName
a3ComQosCtrlName.description: A textual name for the control.

a3ComQosCtrlServiceLevel.name: a3ComQosCtrlServiceLevel
a3ComQosCtrlServiceLevel.description: The service level for all conforming packets.

a3ComQosCtrlConformPktsLossEligible.name: a3ComQosCtrlConformPktsLossEligible
a3ComQosCtrlConformPktsLossEligible.description: The variable indicates whether conforming packets are loss eligible.

a3ComQosCtrlExcessPktsServiceLevel.name: a3ComQosCtrlExcessPktsServiceLevel
a3ComQosCtrlExcessPktsServiceLevel.description: The service level of excess packets for this control.

a3ComQosCtrlExcessPktsLossEligible.name: a3ComQosCtrlExcessPktsLossEligible
a3ComQosCtrlExcessPktsLossEligible.description: The variable indicates whether excess packets are loss eligible.

a3ComQosCtrl8021pTag.name: a3ComQosCtrl8021pTag
a3ComQosCtrl8021pTag.description: This indicates the tag to use on forwarded frames.

a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitType.name: a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitType
a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitType.description: The rate limit type to use with this control. A value of none(1) indicates that no rate limit is set for this control. A value of receivePort(2) indicates that the configured rate limit is applied on a per-port basis. A value of aggregate(3) indicates that the configured rate limit is aggregated across the set of ports that are configured for the rate limit. For values other than none(1), the rate limit entries are created via the a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitTable.

a3ComQosCtrlRowStatus.name: a3ComQosCtrlRowStatus
a3ComQosCtrlRowStatus.description: The status column for this control entry. This object can be set to: createAndGo(4) destroy(6) The following value may be read: active(1) Setting this object to createAndGo(4) creates a row in this table. Setting this object to destroy(6) will remove this entry. Note that a control can only be deleted if it is not attached to a flow or a non-flow classifier. A side effect of deleting a control in this table is the deletion of the corresponding rate limit entries in the a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitTable.

a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitTable.name: a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitTable
a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitTable.description: A list of QoS control rate limits defined on a given system.

a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitEntry.name: a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitEntry
a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitEntry.description: An entry describing a single QoS control rate limit.

a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitCtrlIndex.name: a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitCtrlIndex
a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitCtrlIndex.description: The control index for which this entry is valid.

a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitIndex.name: a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitIndex
a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitIndex.description: The rate limit for which this entry is valid.

a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitPercent.name: a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitPercent
a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitPercent.description: The rate limit as a percentage of input port bandwidth. Packets received in excess of specified rate limit will receive the service defined by value of a3ComQosCtrlExcessPktsServiceLevel object. A value of 0 indicates no rate limit. A value of 101 indicates that this object is not being used and the value of the a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitKbps object will determine the rate limit (if any).

a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitKbps.name: a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitKbps
a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitKbps.description: The rate limit in kilobits per second of input port bandwidth. Packets received in excess of specified rate limit will receive the service defined by value of a3ComQosCtrlExcessPktsServiceLevel object. Note that the requested rate may be rounded up to the next 1/16th chunk bandwidth. Note that the user can specify the rate limit either as a percentage (via the a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitPercent object) or as kilobits per second (via this object) but not both. If the value of the a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitPercent object is 101, then the setting of this object determines the rate limit. A value of -1 for this object indicates no rate limit. Any other value indicates the desired rate limit.

a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitPorts.name: a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitPorts
a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitPorts.description: A bit mask of interfaces that support the defined rate limit. Each interface is represented by a single bit. If that bit is set then the corresponding interface is a member of this control. The bits are assigned with the least significant bit of the first byte corresponding to ifIndex 1, the next bit corresponding to ifIndex 2 and so on. Note that each port can only be associated with a single rate limit per control. An error will be returned if the user tries to assign a port that already has a rate limit associated with it.

a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitRowStatus.name: a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitRowStatus
a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitRowStatus.description: The status column for this rate limit entry. This object can be set to: createAndGo(4) destroy(6) The following value may be read: active(1) Setting this object to createAndGo(4) creates a row in this table. Note that a request to create a new entry must use the next sequential available a3ComQosCtrlRateLimitIndex value. Setting this object to destroy(6) will remove this entry.

a3ComQosRsvpStatus.name: a3ComQosRsvpStatus
a3ComQosRsvpStatus.description: The status of the RSVP protocol.

a3ComQosRsvpMaxTotalResvdBandwidth.name: a3ComQosRsvpMaxTotalResvdBandwidth
a3ComQosRsvpMaxTotalResvdBandwidth.description: The maximum total reservable bandwidth of the output link.

a3ComQosRsvpMaxPerResvBandwidth.name: a3ComQosRsvpMaxPerResvBandwidth
a3ComQosRsvpMaxPerResvBandwidth.description: The maximum per-reservation bandwidth of the output link.

a3ComQosRsvpPolicy.name: a3ComQosRsvpPolicy
a3ComQosRsvpPolicy.description: The indication of a policing option that shows when excess packets are dropped.

a3ComQosRsvpExcessTrafficPolicy.name: a3ComQosRsvpExcessTrafficPolicy
a3ComQosRsvpExcessTrafficPolicy.description: The indication of service for excess packets.

a3ComQosRsvpExcessPktsLossEligible.name: a3ComQosRsvpExcessPktsLossEligible
a3ComQosRsvpExcessPktsLossEligible.description: This object indicates if excess packets are loss eligible.

a3ComQosRsvpAuthentication.name: a3ComQosRsvpAuthentication
a3ComQosRsvpAuthentication.description: This object indicates the status of RSVP authentication.

a3ComQosRsvpMd5Key.name: a3ComQosRsvpMd5Key
a3ComQosRsvpMd5Key.description: The MD5 encryption key. This value is used if the a3ComQosRsvpAuthStatus object is set to enabled(1).

a3ComQosStatsInterval.name: a3ComQosStatsInterval
a3ComQosStatsInterval.description: The time interval, in seconds, over which rate statistics are collected. A value of zero implies absolute (i.e. raw) statistics.

a3ComQosXmtStatsTable.name: a3ComQosXmtStatsTable
a3ComQosXmtStatsTable.description: This table contains QoS transmit rate statistics. The interval over which the rate is calculated is determined by the value of a3ComQosStatsInterval object.

a3ComQosXmtStatsEntry.name: a3ComQosXmtStatsEntry
a3ComQosXmtStatsEntry.description: An entry containing transmit rate statistics.

a3ComQosXmtStatsQindex.name: a3ComQosXmtStatsQindex
a3ComQosXmtStatsQindex.description: The type of transmit queue for which this entry is valid.

a3ComQosXmtStatsLowLossPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtStatsLowLossPkts
a3ComQosXmtStatsLowLossPkts.description: The rate of low loss packets. Low loss packets are packets that are not marked as loss eligible (a3ComQosCtrlConformPktLossEligible object) and are under the threshold. The rate is specified in packets per second.

a3ComQosXmtStatsLowLossDelayedPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtStatsLowLossDelayedPkts
a3ComQosXmtStatsLowLossDelayedPkts.description: The rate of low loss delayed packets. Low loss delayed packets are packets that are not marked as loss eligible (a3ComQosCtrlConformPktLossEligible object) and are over the threshold. The rate is specified in packets per second.

a3ComQosXmtStatsLowLossDiscardedPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtStatsLowLossDiscardedPkts
a3ComQosXmtStatsLowLossDiscardedPkts.description: The rate of low loss discarded packets. Low loss discarded packets are packets that are discarded due to the queue being full. The rate is specified in packets per second.

a3ComQosXmtStatsHighLossPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtStatsHighLossPkts
a3ComQosXmtStatsHighLossPkts.description: The rate of high loss packets. High loss packets are packets that are marked as loss eligible (a3ComQosCtrlConformPktLossEligible object) and are under the threshold. The rate is specified in packets per second.

a3ComQosXmtStatsHighLossDiscardedPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtStatsHighLossDiscardedPkts
a3ComQosXmtStatsHighLossDiscardedPkts.description: The rate of high loss discarded packets. High loss discarded packets are packets that are marked as loss eligible (a3ComQosCtrlConformPktLossEligible object) and are over the threshold. The rate is specified in packets per second.

a3ComQosXmtHmStatsTable.name: a3ComQosXmtHmStatsTable
a3ComQosXmtHmStatsTable.description: This table contains QoS transmit high water mark rate statistics. The interval over which the rate is calculated is determined by the value of a3ComQosStatsInterval object.

a3ComQosXmtHmStatsEntry.name: a3ComQosXmtHmStatsEntry
a3ComQosXmtHmStatsEntry.description: An entry containing transmit high water mark rate statistics.

a3ComQosXmtHmStatsQindex.name: a3ComQosXmtHmStatsQindex
a3ComQosXmtHmStatsQindex.description: The type of queue for which this entry is valid.

a3ComQosXmtHmStatsLowLossPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtHmStatsLowLossPkts
a3ComQosXmtHmStatsLowLossPkts.description: The high mark for low loss packets.

a3ComQosXmtHmStatsLowLossDelayedPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtHmStatsLowLossDelayedPkts
a3ComQosXmtHmStatsLowLossDelayedPkts.description: The high mark for low loss delayed packets.

a3ComQosXmtHmStatsLowLossDiscardedPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtHmStatsLowLossDiscardedPkts
a3ComQosXmtHmStatsLowLossDiscardedPkts.description: The high mark for low loss discarded packets.

a3ComQosXmtHmStatsHighLossPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtHmStatsHighLossPkts
a3ComQosXmtHmStatsHighLossPkts.description: The high mark for high loss packets.

a3ComQosXmtHmStatsHighLossDiscardedPkts.name: a3ComQosXmtHmStatsHighLossDiscardedPkts
a3ComQosXmtHmStatsHighLossDiscardedPkts.description: The high mark for high loss discarded packets.

a3ComQosRcvStatsTable.name: a3ComQosRcvStatsTable
a3ComQosRcvStatsTable.description: A table containing QoS receive rate statistics. The interval over which the rate is calculated is determined by the value of a3ComQosStatsInterval object.

a3ComQosRcvStatsEntry.name: a3ComQosRcvStatsEntry
a3ComQosRcvStatsEntry.description: An entry containing receive rate statistics for a particular port.

a3ComQosRcvStatsConformBytesTotal.name: a3ComQosRcvStatsConformBytesTotal
a3ComQosRcvStatsConformBytesTotal.description: The total conforming bytes receive rate. The rate is in bytes per second.

a3ComQosRcvStatsNonConformBytesForFlows.name: a3ComQosRcvStatsNonConformBytesForFlows
a3ComQosRcvStatsNonConformBytesForFlows.description: The non-conforming bytes receive rate for flows. The rate is in bytes per second.

a3ComQosRcvStatsNonConformBytesForNonFlo.name: a3ComQosRcvStatsNonConformBytesForNonFlows
a3ComQosRcvStatsNonConformBytesForNonFlo.description: The non-conforming bytes receive rate for non-flows. The rate is in bytes per second.

a3ComQosRcvStatsDroppedPkts.name: a3ComQosRcvStatsDroppedPkts
a3ComQosRcvStatsDroppedPkts.description: The number of packets dropped. The rate is specified in packets per second.

a3ComQosBandwidthRatio.name: a3ComQosBandwidthRatio
a3ComQosBandwidthRatio.description: The bandwidth ratio of HighPriority/(HighPriority+BestEffort) that is allocated for each output port on a given system. The value is represented as a percentage.

a3ComQosExcessTrafficClassTag.name: a3ComQosExcessTrafficClassTag
a3ComQosExcessTrafficClassTag.description: This object indicates the IEEE802.1p traffic class value to use to retag excess packets.

a3ComQosFlowClassIntrudingEvent.name: a3ComQosFlowClassIntrudingEvent
a3ComQosFlowClassIntrudingEvent.description: The trap that is generated when a intruder tries to enter a classified network
